The National Energy Board said hearingsinto Hydro-Quebec's request to sell power to the United Stateswill reopen in Ottawa April nine.    The board heard nine days of testimony in Montreal after itopened the hearings March 16.    Hydro-Quebec is seeking an export license to sell 70terawatt hours of electricity to the New England Power Pool, agroup of about 90 utilities, from the year 1990 to 2000. Thecontract is valued at three billion Canadian dlrs. A terawatthour is the power consumed by a city of 100,000 people in oneyear, or 70 billion kilowatt hours.    The hearings are scheduled to last two days in Ottawa.    After that, the board will begin its deliberations, whichcould take as long as two months before a decision is reached. Reuter&#3;